The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, April 18 (PTI): The Indian Armys peacekeeping forces in Congo rescued six injured passengers of an aircraft that crashed in North Kivu province.          
	The rescue team of the sixth battalion of the Sikh Light Infantry, led by Colonel S.A. Sharma, also retrieved 18 bodies and brought the blaze under control. Forty people died in the crash.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Senior BJP leader Vijay Goel was appointed its general secretary on Friday. The seat was lying vacant after Om Mathur was appointed chief of the BJPs Rajasthan unit.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): The parents of four-month-old Khushi, who refused to accept her despite a positive DNA test, have been arrested on the charge of abandoning her. In December 2007, Sheila and Raj Mani Jaiswal had refused to take her home, alleging that the Sion Hospital authorities had swapped their baby boy for a girl.                  
	Rameshwaram (PTI): Two Sri Lankans and an Indian have been arrested for trying to smuggle 14 tractor front-wheel tyres to Sri Lanka.                                                                                                                       
